>|> When I was in the US-Navy (as a peon-class crypto-clerk) I heard of a
>|> form of "rice paper" used by some spies.
>|> 
>|> The concept was the same as flash-paper (quick emergency destruction!)
>|> but instead of applying fire, you applied WATER.  Supposedly, this stuff
>|> would then melt into an amorphous glob of rice pudding.  I'd guess that
